# Migrations

- Location: `migrations/`. Format: `NNNNNN_description.up.sql` + matching `.down.sql`.
- Next version: one higher than the highest existing `NNNNNN`.
- Embedded at runtime via `migrations/embed.go`; applied with `make migrate-up` (golang-migrate).
- **Never modify** migrations already applied in shared environments—add a new migration instead.

## SQL style

- `uuid` PKs, `timestamptz` for timestamps, `jsonb` for flexible specs (see `infrastructure_hardwares.specs`).
- Snake_case table/column names matching Go `db` tags in `types.go`.
- Add indexes for FKs and common filters. Name constraints explicitly when non-obvious.

After schema change, update the matching `postgres_repository.go` column consts and scan functions in the same PR.
